**Our interpretation:**

After analysis, we understand the requirement as follows:

1. **The 5 columns are building blocks** — They are used to DEFINE scopes, not to be exposed as user-facing filters.

2. **Scopes are the primary concept** — Users think in terms of "I want to see US data" rather than "I want to filter by accounting_site = 12309".

3. **"Adapt any time as users" means:**
   - Users can SWITCH between scopes instantly (US → Fortis → BCeF → Japan)
   - Users can view "All" data if needed
   - It does NOT mean users need to BUILD custom filters themselves

4. **Simple UI** — A single "Scope" dropdown with options: All, US, Fortis, BCeF, Japan.

---

**Why this interpretation?**

• The scope definitions are business concepts, not ad-hoc filters
• BCeF logic (NOT IN + IS NULL) is too complex for manual Tableau filtering
• Fortis has 200+ accounting codes — impractical as a multi-select filter
• Exposing 5 technical columns would confuse end users

